PeptideProphetSearch

public PeptideProphetSearch(java.lang.String aPrecursor_mass_type,
                            java.lang.String aFragment_mass_type,
                            java.lang.String aEnzyme_name,
                            int aMax_number_internal_cleavages,
                            int aMin_number_termini,
                            java.util.HashMap aModifications,
                            java.util.HashMap aParameters,
                            java.lang.String aSearch_db_name,
                            java.lang.String aSearch_db_type,
                            java.lang.String aSearch_engine)
This constructor takes arguments read from the 'search_summary' section in a PeptideProphet output file.

Parameters:
aPrecursor_mass_type - String with the precursor mass type ('average' or 'monoisotopic').
aFragment_mass_type - String with the fragment mass type. ('average' or 'monoisotopic').
aEnzyme_name - String with the name of the search enzyme used.
aMax_number_internal_cleavages - int with the maximal number of allowed internal cleavages for the search enzyme used.
aMin_number_termini - int with the minimal number of correct enzymatic termini a peptide should contain.
aModifications - HashMap with the modifications used. Keys should be the modification code, values should be PeptideProphetModification instances.
aParameters - HashMap with parameters. The keys should be parameter names, the values parameter values.
aSearch_db_name - String with the database name.
aSearch_db_type - String with the databse type ('AA' or 'NA').
aSearch_engine - String with the name of he search engine used.
